    • Constructor Detail

      • ViewR

        public ViewR()
        A public constructor for ViewR that creates multiple BufferedImages for our game, as well as scaling those BufferedImages. It also sets setFocusable to true and it sets setFocusTraversalKeysEnabled to false. Lastly, it creates a new Jframe().

        A method that is used to update the view.
        Parameters:
        playerx, - The x cord of the player is set equal to the boat's x cord
        netx, - The x cord of the net is set equal to the net's x cord
        nety, - The y cord of the net is set equal to the net's y cord
        polelength, - the int poleLength is set equal to the poleLength
        o, - An arrayList of Entities that is used by objs in the view. Represents all objects.
        score, - An int that is used by the score in the view
        timer, - An int that is used by the timer in the view
        caughtNums, - An array of int's that is used by caughtNums in the view
        lastCaught, - A string that is used by lastCaught in the view
        caught, - An arrayList of Entities that is used by caught. Represents the caught animals.
        pointerx, - A double that is used by pox in the View.
        reading, - A double that is used by reading in the View.
        measured, - An arrayList of Entities that is used by measured. Represents the measured animals.
        factDisplayed, - An array of int's that is used by factsDisplayed in the view.
        factLocations, - An arrayList of Points that is used by factLocations in the view.
        mapAnimals, - An arrayList of Entities that is used by mapAnimals in the view.
        mappedAnimals, - An array of boolean's that is used by mappedAnimals in the view.
